[{"id":33219,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Area Under Curves","question":"","options":["$\\frac{13}{3}$","$\\frac{10}{3}$","$\\frac{5}{3}$","$\\frac{8}{3}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"The intersection point of $y=x-2$ and $y=\\sqrt{x}$ is $(4,2)$.\nThe required area\n$$\n=\\int_0^4 \\sqrt{x} d x-\\frac{1}{2} \\times 2 \\times 2=\\frac{16}{3}-2=\\frac{10}{3}\n$$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/vIwh5NSviP1EpWack9vseRpA7D9EWyWMySayl42G1DY.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null},{"id":33177,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Area Under Curves","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6d783e6c-47e0-4b78-9510-b0f1ba1f446c-1.png\" style=\"width: 259px; height: 188px;\" /></p><p>Given, the equation of line,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>And the line&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo></math></p><p>The intersection point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Area of triangle is half the total area&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msubsup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msubsup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>39</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>39</mn><mn>18</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Then,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mi>m</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>39</mn><mn>18</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>12</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>26</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":33136,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Area Under Curves","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Let, the parabola be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>,</p><p>Now given parabola is passing through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Now putting the value in the above equation of parabola we get,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Now solving above three equations we get,</p><p>Parabola as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>Now area of region between&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#8804;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;is given by,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5f6a2e8d-9d16-4fee-bdda-5b832bc2d93b.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 251px;\" /></p><p>Now from above diagram, required area will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>0</mn></msubsup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>A</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":33092,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Area Under Curves","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ZAORk50s0lcQI7sRAdHl4N_DJSUcRHOTjaxCpVZdMyU.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>$\\begin{aligned} & \\text { Required Area }=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 2 \\times 2+\\frac{1}{2} \\times 3 \\times 3+\\frac{1}{2} \\times 1 \\times 11 \\\\ & =12\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":33169,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Area Under Curves","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Plotting the diagram of given data we have,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5abbd284-9087-4828-aaa5-38068de8f49e-image.png\" style=\"width: 210px; height: 150px;\" /></p><p>Now finding limit by diagram, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>So total area will be given by,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mn>0</mn></msubsup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>0</mn><mn>1</mn></msubsup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>Now for solving&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8747;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>&nbsp;Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#8747;</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p>Now putting the limit and solving we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>64</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>36</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>256</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>256</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mrow><mi>&#960;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>36</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":33208,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Area Under Curves","question":"","options":["<math><mn>30</mn></math>","<math><mn>18</mn></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>53</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mn>16</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>We have to find the area of the region&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>:</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Now, to find the point of intersection of the curves&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;we equate the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;to get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p>And, the graph of the given functions is as</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/55ab0f66-2ac5-432b-8e18-f7c112d82f48-image.png\" style=\"width: 210px; height: 223px;\" /></p><p>The shaded area is the required area, and&nbsp;</p><p>Area<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></msubsup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>l</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></msubsup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></math></p><p>Now, using&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8747;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;we get</p><p>Area<math><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mrow><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msubsup></math></p><p><math><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>32</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn></math>&nbsp;sq units.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":33213,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Area Under Curves","question":"","options":["$\\frac{8}{3}$","$\\frac{37}{24}$","$\\frac{187}{24}$","$\\frac{14}{3}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fYoggIIYGTN6xBD6Qx3VBLkKetcriHuvr-bQe0fp3es.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\r\n\r\nThe equation of parabola $x^{2}=y-1$\r\n\r\nThe equation of tangent at (2,5) to parabola is\r\n\r\n$y-5=\\left(\\frac{d y}{d x}\\right)_{(2,5)}(x-2)$\r\n\r\n$y-5=4(x-2)$\r\n\r\n$4 x-y=3$\r\n\r\nThen, the required area\r\n\r\n$=\\int_{0}^{2}\\left\\{\\left(x^{2}+1\\right)-(4 x-3)\\right\\} d x-$ Area of $\\Delta A O D$\r\n\r\n$=\\int_{0}^{2}\\left(x^{2}-4 x+4\\right) d x-\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{3}{4} \\times 3$\r\n\r\n$=\\left[\\frac{(x-2)^{3}}{3}\\right]_{0}^{2}-\\frac{9}{8}=\\frac{37}{24}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null}]